r not, as long as they are not\ntoo severe, but devoted to duty,\n\n(1-7) Thus conduct thyself 'This is the rule. This is the teaching. This is\nthe true purport (Upanishad) of the Veda. This is the command. Thus should you\nobserve. Thus should this be observed.'\n\n* * *\n\n### Footnotes\n\n[53:1](sbe15032.htm#fr_211) Aparaprayukta iti svatantra _h_. For other\nrenderings, see Weber, Ind. Stud. II, p. 216.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: I, 12](sbe15033.htm)\n\n"